# Enhancement Plan — AI Secure Data Intelligence Platform

Upgrade the existing platform with 11 innovations: root cause analysis, fix suggestions, WebSockets, AI chat, visual charts, timeline, attack patterns, cross-log correlation, and smart alerts.

---

## New Backend Packages
- `ws` — WebSocket server for real-time log streaming

## New Frontend Packages
- `recharts` — React charts for risk dashboard

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend New Modules

#### [NEW] src/modules/rootCauseEngine.js
Maps each finding type → `rootCause` (why it happened) + `fixSuggestions` (how to fix).
- Static knowledge base covering all 15+ detection types
- Returns structured `{ rootCause, fixSuggestions[] }` per finding

#### [NEW] src/modules/attackPatternEngine.js
Temporal + repetition pattern analysis:
- Brute force: ≥3 login failures → details with IP, count, timespan
- API abuse: repeated identical requests within window
- Credential stuffing: multiple users failing same IP
- Returns severity-scored attack patterns with descriptions

#### [NEW] src/modules/correlationEngine.js
Cross-log analysis across multiple findings:
- Groups findings by IP address
- Identifies same credential across multiple lines
- Detects repeated attack signatures
- Returns correlation clusters with confidence scores

#### [NEW] src/websocket/streamServer.js
- Attaches `ws` WebSocket server to Express HTTP server
- Accepts client connections, authenticates via token query param
- Emits real-time log events as JSON frames: `{ type, line, finding, timestamp }`
- Broadcasts high-risk alerts to all connected clients
- Supports chunked file streaming (large log simulation)

#### [NEW] src/routes/chat.js
`POST /chat` — AI security chatbot:
- Accepts `{ message, sessionId?, context? }`
- Sends to Python AI service `/ai/chat` endpoint
- Falls back to rule-based answers for common questions:
  - "what risks" → summarize last session findings
  - "how to fix" → return fix suggestions
  - "why dangerous" → return root causes
- Persists conversation to `chat_messages` DB table

#### [NEW] src/routes/alerts.js
- `GET /alerts` — user's alerts (unread first)
- `PATCH /alerts/:id/read` — mark read
- `GET /alerts/stats` — count by severity

#### [MODIFY] server.js
Attach `ws.Server` to the HTTP server after `app.listen()`.

#### [MODIFY] src/routes/analyze.js
Enrich each finding with `rootCause` and `fixSuggestions` from rootCauseEngine.
Run `attackPatternEngine` on combined findings. Persist alerts for high/critical findings.

